$ .gitattributes

code {
*.cpp      eol=lf
*.png      binary
code }

{ linguist

  `linguist-…` provides a way for → https://github.com/github-linguist/linguist/blob/master/docs/overrides.md[custom override stategies for language definitions and file paths].

  { linguist-language

    `linguist-language` identify/override the assumed language depending on the extension (for example by → development/version-control-systems/git/github which uses the → development/version-control-systems/git/github#github-linguist[linguist library to identify languages in a repository]).

     For example, the following three lines make sure that `*.bas`, `*.cls` and `*.frm` are counted as → development/languages/VBA[Visual Basic for Application] (VBA) source code:
code {
*.bas linguist-language=vba
*.cls linguist-language=vba
*.frm linguist-language=vba
code }

   

  See also → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/VBAModules/issues/1[this issue] in the → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/VBAModules[VBAModules Github repository].

  }

}

links:
  This → https://github.com/gitattributes/gitattributes[Github repository] claims to collect useful `.gitattribute` templates.
